				"endColumn": 10
			},
			"contents": [
				{
					"value": "Regular Expression just like `\"match\"`  \nStarts a region that _can_ span multiple lines. When used in conjunction with a `\"end\"`/`\"while\"` key  \nRules can be nested inside the block with the `\"patterns\"` key  \nAn anchor is placed after the `\"begin\"` rule; that you can then match with `\\\\G`  \n**\\*WARNING\\*** If `\"begin\"` matches the newline `\\n`. The `\\\\G` anchor is then placed at the beginning of the _next_ line  \n\n```json-textmate-regex\nExample: (\\\\s*)(#*)(\\\")\n```\n---\n[Translation](https://github.com/slevithan/oniguruma-to-es) from [Oniguruma](https://github.com/kkos/oniguruma/blob/master/doc/RE) to [JavaScript](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Regular_expressions): \n```javascript\n/\"/v\n```\n",
					"supportThemeIcons": false,
					"supportHtml": false,
					"supportAlertSyntax": false,
					"uris": {
						"https://github.com/slevithan/oniguruma-to-es": {
							"$mid": 1,
							"path": "/slevithan/oniguruma-to-es",
							"scheme": "https",
