			"contents": [
				{
					"value": "Regular Expression just like `\"match\"`  \nEnds the block started by `\"begin\"`  \n`\"end\"` has priority over rules inside the `\"patterns\"` array  \n**\\*WARNING\\*** Rules inside `\"patterns\"` can 'overmatch' the `\"end\"` rule. Effectively 'pushing' it out  \n(Captures) inside the `\"begin\"` key can be referenced here with regex back-references `\\\\1`  \n\n```json-textmate-regex\nExample: (\\\")(\\\\2)\n```\n---\n[Translation](https://github.com/slevithan/oniguruma-to-es) from [Oniguruma](https://github.com/kkos/oniguruma/blob/master/doc/RE) to [JavaScript](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Regular_expressions): \n```javascript\n/\"/v\n```\n",
